              "orphans": 2,
              "widows": 2
            }
          },
          {
            "allowLineSplit": true,
            "content": "Once the cursor clears the foot of the float, the full column width is restored. The transition is seamless: the same text box holds lines of varying widths, driven by per-line data stored in the _lineWidths array. No element boundary coincides with the float boundary, and no special-casing is needed in the renderer. The resolver tracks state in a local closure and relies on wrapRichSegments calling it with strictly ascending line indices.",
            "keepWithNext": false,
