            "allowLineSplit": true,
            "content": "An amber square occupies the left margin here, with body text filling the wider right column. PageMaker pioneered this runaround layout in 1985, bringing professional typesetting to the Macintosh. The SpatialMap knows only rectangles and their wrap modes; the rest is interval arithmetic — subtract the obstacle’s X range from the available column width and assign the remainder to each line.",
